My city is big. My neighborhood has many different kinds of places. Shops and offices are next to homes. There are many places to eat and shop. Some stores are big, some are small.

There are parks near my home. People take their children to the parks. Many different people live in my neighborhood. There are LGBTQ+ people, Jewish people, and people from the former Soviet Union.

Other parts of the city have groups of people from other countries. There is Korea town, China town, and Little Armenia. It takes a long time to drive between these places because traffic is bad. 

Most people drive in my city. Few people walk. There are many new buildings. Some people are happy, others are not. They worry about more people and more cars.

There are many kinds of homes in my city. Some are big, some are small. Some are houses, some are apartments.

I do not know most of my neighbors. My neighborhood is not close like it was when I was a child.

My area is interesting. Most houses are for one family. But some homes are split in two, still joined. My house has a small yard in front and a small driveway on the side. It is like the others, showing a time when living in the suburbs was the American dream. This dream seemed good for everyone, but it feels different now.  Still, my area and others like it say the dream is still here. People are still trying to hold onto it. People are not as happy as they were. Yards are not as neat. But there are cars in every driveway. Kids still play like the world is all around them. The public school is almost ninety years old. It is still there. It makes the kids think about the future and reminds older people of the past. There are not many churches, mostly empty. But the basketball courts are full. The houses look different, but they feel the same. There is a big store called Super "A". It is owned by a big family from Yemen. They are probably the only Arab family in the area. Most people are African American. The streets are wide and kids play football. They stop only for cars. Most people in my area have lived here for a long time. They can tell stories about when everyone knew everyone. There was a karate school, but kids stopped going when Hollywood stopped making karate movies. Now it is a pharmacy. Drugs are good, I have heard. There is a small movie theater that shows old movies for less money. Young people do not go because they want new movies. Older people like it because it is cheap. There is one highway that goes through our town. The entrances and exits are in the next town.  There was a plan to make exits for our town, but the young people wanted it, and the older people said no. They said the highway would ruin the town. They told the city council to say no. They are building a new high school. We are trying to choose a mascot. I think a cyborg with a country accent and a log cabin would be good.

This area looks quiet. It is near stores, not a place to live. But behind the old building, past the hotels open only for family visits, there is a big community. It is hidden.

Apartment buildings stand close together. They look like Russian nesting dolls, placed side by side. Some buildings are bad. We will not talk about them. But the next buildings are very different. A small college is nearby. Students go there. They drink coffee and go to class. Cars drive by and get angry at the students.

The road goes to another street. A park is on one side, and a place to heal broken bones is on the other. People sit on the porch with fans. Children play in the park. Old people walk dogs and watch the young people. 

There are stores near the park. A place to eat sushi, a place for swimming supplies, and a place for nails. You can eat, buy things, and get a manicure, all in one place. 

There is also a place for frozen yogurt. The young people eat it and ride skateboards. This area is like a picture from the past.

She asked, "Where is everything?" We drove past the corn fields. The fields went on and on. I knew she would be surprised. She was from a town where you could walk to the store. She had never seen so much open space.  I told her about growing up in rural Ohio. In that moment, she understood me better. 

We drove down a small road.  You will see a lake. Just past the lake is my home. My neighborhood has small houses made of brick and stucco. Each house has a lot of land. People take pride in keeping their yards nice. In the spring, there are many flowers. The trees change color with each season.  The driveways have expensive cars. They shine in the sun after a wash.

My neighbor, who is Korean, lives near my house. He is always outside. He mows his lawn all day. You can hear him singing. Everyone laughs at him, but he is a kind man. He was a doctor before. Now he works with his lawn mower. It looks like a big green tractor.

My house is gray.  There are geese in my side yard. My dog chases them. There is a small stream behind my house. You can hear frogs, the water, and cows in the distance.

Across a bridge is a special place. There are trees, plants, and flowers growing there. I played there when I was a child. I built forts and played games. 

Winter is hard here, but it is beautiful. The yard turns brown. The trees have no leaves. When it snows, it looks like a dream. My sister and I built snow forts and made snowmen. We fought a lot, using snowballs as weapons. 

We had a great time. We played pretend and forgot about everything else. We were just happy kids.

Portland, Oregon has a special kind of strange. People say "Keep Portland Weird," this is on a building that sells pizza and serves drinks. It also plays music and lets people dance. The slogan shows people want to keep Portland different. Some people think it means remembering the old Portland, when it was less famous. It was a place for creative people. Others think it means come to Portland and be different. You will be accepted.

Portland is still weird, even with new people moving here. Many people from California have moved to Portland to live. They build new houses for people to live in. But Portland is still unique.

"Weird" does not mean everyone is always nice. It means accepting things that are not normal. Portland has many things like other cities. People buy things made in China. There are many ways to be unique. Portland has people who do yoga, people who like fashion, and people who work in offices. Maybe weird means people in Portland do not take things so seriously.

In my neighborhood, houses are brightly colored. People grow flowers, herbs, and vegetables in their gardens. In the summer, there are boxes on the sidewalk. People put things they do not want in these boxes. They can be clothes, books, or anything. It is like a surprise gift.

Walking around my neighborhood is fun. There are many different kinds of people in Portland. Some people like yoga with goats, some people like soccer. People in Portland like many things.

Portland has problems like drug use and homelessness. These problems are caused by mental health issues. The rain and cloudy weather might make these problems worse. Portland tries to help people who do not have homes, but there are not enough services.

Some people in Portland are kind to homeless people, others are not. This is not unique to Portland.

The mountains are always there. They are in the north. They see the sun each morning and each evening. No matter if I forget them or am busy, they are there. They are strong and do not change. When I am stressed, I look at them. They help me feel better. I first came here for school. The mountains north of the school are beautiful. The school is pretty too, with its buildings, ponds, and trees. But the mountains are the best. The town is nice too. There are many cafes where I studied. You can walk or take the bus to the center of town. The old buildings look like they are from a long time ago. The town is busy like a big city. 

But if you walk past the library, you are back in a small town. The town has two different feels that are close together. This makes it special. I have many memories here. 

I walk past the old swings in the park with my friends. We go to the movies in the fancy theater. But there are sad memories too. The ponds are good for thinking and crying. I spend time watching turtles and ducks. I think about my life. I walk past the pond and the park and the houses. Then I see the sun shining on the palm trees. I am walking north. The mountains are there. They are strong and tall. They make me feel like I can do anything.

If you go to Bensonhurst in Brooklyn, it is easy to find. Public transit is good. It is a popular way to travel in New York City. Bensonhurst is an urban area. You will feel like you are still in New York City.

During your visit, see the many Asian stores. Many Asian people have moved to Bensonhurst in the last twenty years. You will see an Asian store on almost every block. Supermarkets and laundry shops are popular.

These stores are good for local people. Food is good, prices are low, and it is very convenient. There are four Asian supermarkets near me. They are all within two minutes of each other. This is very helpful for getting food.

Bensonhurst has people from many places. There are immigrants and their children. Many big businesses are owned by Asian people.

There is also a new park. It has ten basketball courts, a big field, handball courts, swings, a playground, and a water fountain.

The park is diverse. People of all kinds play there. There are not many big buildings in Bensonhurst. The buildings are for apartments or homes. Most people live in two-family houses.

Most people are nice, but it can be noisy. Cars play loud music and drive fast.

If you visit at night, be careful. Bensonhurst is safe, but people can be mean. You may meet people who want to fight or steal. I was bullied here many years ago. Recently, there have been reports of stolen packages.

People do not always clean up after their dogs, even though there is a fine for doing so.

You will see dog waste on the streets. Look out for it!

My house is at the top of a big hill. People call it the "work out hill" because runners like to run up it. There are no sidewalks, so people walk on the road. The road is bad in some places. Some wires are old and broken. It rains a lot, so the wires are often fixed. There are many tall trees. People want to cut them down because they block the view of the ocean. Many houses are high up to see the ocean. The sunset is beautiful. The water is lit up, and the sky is orange. It is often cloudy, so the sun is not always bright. It is often wet.

There are not many children. There are many old people. People have dogs. They run in the yards. Be careful, they might go into your house! Rabbits live here, too. Gardens do not like them. My cats catch them. We have birds, too. Sparrows, hummingbirds, and sometimes hawks or eagles. 

There are no stores near my house. If you walk down to the water, there are some restaurants. The beach is small. The rocks are fun to throw in the water. The bay is not wide. You can see the other side.

I live in a small town in Tennessee. My home is in a quiet area. It is near two big roads. We see many cars each day. I know most of the people who live near me. They do normal things like work in their yards. In winter, we use a hill to sled. We live at the beginning of our street. We see many cars every day. We remember new cars. Some people walk for exercise. Children ride bikes. My family is home often. There are four of us: me, my wife, and our two daughters. They are eleven and fourteen years old. People know us well. We play outside, even in the rain. We often cook outside. It smells good. Many people cut grass. You can hear the sound of mowers from March until October. 

We have many trees. They make shade. In fall, there are many leaves. We rake and burn them. I like the smell of burning leaves. It means fall is here. This year, we have not had much cold weather.

Our garage is behind our house. We use the front door only when someone visits. I work in the garage on my truck. When the doors are open, I feel closer to my neighborhood. Our street is quiet on holidays. On Thanksgiving, people visit from other places. There are many cars. It is the same on Mother's Day and Christmas. I like living here. It would be better if it was not a busy road.

My area is in the center of the high desert. There is a lot of dirt. People who have not lived here may not understand. The color is always brown. If you see a green lawn, it means someone spends a lot of money on it.

When I first lived here in the 1990s, houses were far apart. Now there are more houses, but they are still spread out. It looks more like a city now, but many places are changing.

Most people are friendly. Like any place, there are good parts and bad parts. I live in a nice area with many friendly older people. 

The stores are big chains like Food 4 Less and Smart & Final. For smaller stores, you have to travel. I do not see many Whole Foods or similar stores.

I think many people work in construction. The city is not very built up, so there is still a lot of space to build. I like it the way it is. I moved from a big city and do not want to go back.

I work in construction as a drywall and T-bar installer.

I like the animals here. People come to the desert for many reasons. One reason is the beauty. The desert has tough environments that need protection. These environments are home to many types of animals. People who live here should learn about these animals to live together safely.

My family and I get along well with the animals. My three children love lizards and desert bugs.

Victorville has some things to see. It is a good place for families to experience the desert.

The San Bernardino County Fair is held here every year. It is a fun event.

You can visit Wrightwood nearby to see snowy mountains.

The Victor Valley Museum has rocks, bones, Native American objects, and things that show the history of Victorville.

My neighborhood is a little different. I live on a college campus. The people in my dorm are my neighbors.  The campus is also my neighborhood, but not as close as my dorm. My neighborhood has houses, people, stores, and parks, just like other neighborhoods.

First, there are three types of houses: apartments, regular houses, and dorm houses. Apartments have 2 to 4 people per room, and there are 4 to 6 rooms per floor. Most apartments have two floors, so about 20 people live in each building.

Regular houses are for rent by anyone connected to the school. They have 2 to 4 bedrooms and mostly alumni live there. There are not many of these houses. Dorm houses are for students. Hundreds of students live in these houses. Two students share a room, except for a few cases. 

My school has many different people. There are people from many cultures and ages. Staff members live in the regular houses. Newer students live in dorms, and older students live in apartments. 

The campus has many stores. There are places to eat, and stores that sell school clothes and food. You can find almost anything you need on campus. 

There is one park on campus. Everyone in the neighborhood uses it. It is clean and safe.

I have lived here for ten years. When I first came to Stockbridge from Riverdale, I was sad. I missed my old home and friends. My parents wanted a better life for me and my sister, so we moved. We got a new house, a good high school, and a safer place to live.

At first, I made new friends and some new enemies at school. I did not get to know many neighbors except for Mr. Glen and his children, and Dennis for a little while. They are good people, like family to me.

I went to Mr. Glen’s wedding with my family. It was fun! I caught a piece of his wife’s dress when she threw it. I hope his wife, Ms. Veda, is happy. I enjoyed dancing with Marsharii, one of their daughters. I hope she is doing well.

My neighborhood is like a maze. I use a GPS to explore it. I have been to the park with my friends, Kason and Curtis. We played video games and had fun.

The park is peaceful. I like to go there to relax. I also practice my balance with sticks from the hardware store and sometimes bring my wooden sword. There is a basketball and tennis court, but I haven’t played in a long time.

My dad taught me and my best friend how to play tennis with Mr. Graves. We had a great time. We worked hard, but we always had fun.

I have had many good times in this neighborhood. I look forward to more happy memories in the future.

My home is near my school. I like living there. There are many apartment buildings. There are also a few restaurants and bars. They are not very expensive. One bar just changed names. It is more expensive, but the drinks are good. Most people are nice. They are students or have low incomes. The rent is low. There are many children near my home. There is a school close by. I do not know my neighbors. I do not want to. They smoke a lot of marijuana. The building managers put air freshener near their door. It is funny. The buildings are old, but may have new insides. Down the street are new apartments. I do not like them. They are not built well, but the rent is high. The buildings are near the school, so the managers can charge more. There is a cheap restaurant nearby. They serve food on paper plates. Most food is warmed up in the microwave. Across the street is a gas station. People say it is a bad place to work. The city fixed the road last summer. Now there is a good sidewalk, grass, and the area is nicer. My building has many trees. They cut down some trees, but there are many left. Behind my building is a line of trees, then another set of apartments. I live on 42nd Street. Behind me is 43rd Street. It is not as nice. The sidewalks are bad. The buildings look old. There are many trees on this street. Maybe they hide the buildings. Most crime in the area has happened at an apartment complex on this street. But I cannot blame them alone. There are other apartments across the street with crime and many people moving in and out. I like where I live. It is affordable and there are many things nearby. I like that the university is walkable and there are two bus stops. I can go to the store and downtown easily.

My area has small houses. They are close together, but they look like they are far apart. All the houses are yellow with white front porches and green roofs. Almost everyone knows each other. We talk in the evenings. The small children play outside. It is nice to be in a place that is not filled with computers and machines. It feels like we are back in time. 

We live near fields and trees. The sky is blue. There are white clouds in the sky. The bad thing is that we have storms. Last week, we had a warning about a tornado. We heard the sirens and went to a safe place.

My small dog went with me. My big dog stayed in the living room and was scared. We heard big hail fall on the ground. After the storm, the road was hot. The hail melted quickly.

After the storm, a rainbow appeared. I took pictures to share with my friends. Then, people came home. Everything was normal again.

I live in a two-bedroom apartment. Everyone else in the area lives in the same kind of apartment. The inside of the apartments are different. Some are small. I like to walk in the big field behind my apartment. There is a pond there. I have seen deer. I hear a big frog sing in the morning.

It is a good place to live. It is close to the city. I hear roosters crow in the morning. It feels like a small village. We even have a donkey that makes noise in the evening. I am happy that I found this place.

I lived in this neighborhood when I started eighth grade. It was hard to make friends at first. I made friends with two boys. One lived two houses down. The other lived on my street.  They do not live here anymore, but I remember them. 

The people who lived here when I moved here are still here. My neighborhood is like other American neighborhoods. There are many two-story houses. On warm days, I hear children playing outside. The neighborhood is quiet most days. I have never had any problems with neighbors. People leave each other alone unless they need help.

I have ordered things online and never had a package taken. I trust my neighbors. There is a park near my house. I have many good memories there. I played basketball, football, and baseball there. I also got hurt there once playing football. But the good memories are better. Now, I go to the park with my cousins' children. They are young and like the swings and slides. Just thinking about the park makes them happy. The park makes me feel nostalgic.

My neighborhood is diverse. There are many kinds of food. Close by, you can find Chinese, Indian, Mexican, and Italian restaurants. Some people use apps like GrubHub and DoorDash to get food. Fast food is popular, but you can find it anywhere. There are many pizza places too.

The stores have everything you need. There are dry cleaners, a Walgreens, a CVS, and a Jewel-Osco grocery store. There is even an Indian store. Overall, I like my neighborhood. Seeing bad things happen to people in other neighborhoods makes me thankful for mine.

My town is small. It is in South Carolina. It is not special. But it has many peach farms. People call it the Peach Capital of the World. Most of the town is farm land. There are peach trees and cows.

The houses are far apart. Many are two stories. They have metal roofs or gray shingles. The houses are not near the road. They are back in the fields. There is one stop light in town. It is at a four way.

There are three places to buy fast food. There is a Chinese restaurant, a Mexican restaurant, and a burger place. There used to be a pizza place, but it closed. There is a small drug store. It is famous for its Cherry Coca-Cola. There is one grocery store, but people often go to a bigger store in another town. The most popular store is Dollar General. It sells many things.

There is a small furniture store. It has been in town for a long time. There is a pet groomer next door. There is a doctor and a vet. They are small but good. There is one elementary school. Students go to school in another town for middle and high school.

There are no parks in town, but they are making one. There are not many things to do in town. There are no movies, bowling, or playgrounds. It is a quiet town.

I first heard of my home when I listened to a podcast about missing people. It was a little strange. Most apartments here cost over a thousand dollars each month. I had not heard that story, and neither had my friends. Maybe it is the hard times. I know some friends cry at night. Things are expensive, but we have learned to save money. You learn to like old toys from the market and clothes that have been kept in storage. You do not smell as much when you are older. You might smoke, or you might just get used to things. But the market is always there. The smell of being an adult is old magazines on a closed piano. It stays in your clothes even after you wash them. 

There are three secondhand stores near here. If you start on one side, you can go to two charity stores, a library, a store for old books, and a shop with strange things. The city center is busy. Cars and people fill the streets every morning, but you cannot hear it in the stores. It does not matter how many cars or people go by, the stores are quiet. It is a good place to spend an afternoon. Every year, there are more people and cars. It is a growing city, they say. It has one of the biggest online stores for buying and selling things. It is still growing and changing. It reminds me of New York. Everyone is working on their own goals, and no one asks much from you. You can be alone, quiet, and independent, and people will leave you alone. It is not like the South, where if you show a little concern, people think you care. No one asks about your life here. You can keep to yourself as long as you want, and the city will keep moving like waves on the beach. It is a lively place.

Between the piano player next door and the two people who sing upstairs, there is always something happening. In a way, we have less of an apartment building full of strangers and more of a community of friends. We help each other, celebrate birthdays, mourn deaths, and help each other when we can. In a way, I am lucky to be here. I like most of my neighbors, and they treat me well. I make sure to clean up after myself and leave them food, and they do the same. I bring them mail, and they bring me mail. It is nice to see them, and I think they like me being here. I live in a big, impersonal city, but it is people like my neighbors that make me feel like I did not ruin my life.

My area is a suburb. It is like many other suburbs. There is a group that looks after the houses. They make sure all the houses are the same.  There are small front yards with grass, rocks, and short drives. Most houses are one story, but some are two stories.

The mailboxes are not like other suburbs. They are all in one place, not in front of each house.  You need a key to open your mailbox. There are also big boxes for packages.

My house is on the edge of the city. It is both suburb and country. There are pools and paths to walk on. You can exercise without going to a park.

The area has many older people. It is safe, and people look out for each other. There are also some middle-aged and young people. The city is big but feels small. It has most stores you need. There is one mall. It is not big, but it has what you need. It takes about fifteen minutes to drive to the mall.

My neighborhood is safe and nice. It has good things like pools and paths.  It is not near many stores, but you can drive to any store you want.

I live in a small town. It is near a big city. My home is in a part of town where people have little money. Most houses are old, and many are rented. But it is a nice place to live. My neighbors are kind. They say hello when they see me. There is some crime here, but not much. A few years ago there were some shootings near my house. One person died. Luckily, my family has not been hurt.

Our town has a big problem with drugs. Many people have died from taking too much medicine. There are places that can help people stop using drugs. There are also classes for people who know someone with a drug problem.

My son goes to a good school. The teachers and staff are great. My son has a disability, but no one has been mean to him. The school is a happy place. 

The town has many things to do. The city workers have fixed the roads and parks. Most of these improvements are in the part of town where stores are. My part of town needs more help.

I like living in this town. People are friendly. The schools are good. We can buy what we need. Our house is not big or expensive, but it is comfortable. We have lived here for many years and like it here.

My neighborhood is full of culture. It is on a hill with old buildings. I live in a tall apartment building. It is across from a old theater. Near my home is a small bar that people like to visit in the summer. Many people wait in line to go there. Not far away is a big park. People live in tents in the park during the winter. It rains a lot in winter. The tents keep them warm. They are near a place where they can shower.

I love my city. It has old buildings and a beautiful view of the ocean. But I love the people most.

My neighborhood was once known for gangs. People still talk about the police who tried to stop the gangs. The people work hard to keep their neighborhood safe. They care about their city. Some people say that white people should not walk alone at night. I think this is wrong. Maybe I look different, or maybe the people see me as one of them. 

I see racism and fear in my city. But I also see kindness. People help each other. They offer me a jacket when I am cold. They let me charge my phone. They give me money when I am sad.

No matter where I go, my neighborhood is always home.

I live in a small town in rural Michigan. It is a place where farmlands meet small tourist areas. There are no big city stores, like malls, Wal-Mart, or Applebee's. If you need to go somewhere, you have to drive. But, I live in a very beautiful place surrounded by water. My town is surrounded by Lake Michigan and Lake Charlevoix. You can find a beach to swim in almost everywhere.  

My neighborhood shows what small towns are like. The houses are spread out, not close together. They are old houses, some updated, some not. Most have full basements. Many houses have old aluminum siding. The houses are all different colors. Most have yards with swings, slides, and sometimes gardens or fences for animals.

The people here work hard, raise families, or have raised families. You see kids playing outside, people walking dogs, and neighbors biking and rollerblading. Everyone knows each other. If you see someone, you wave or smile.

The lawns are well-kept. No leaves are piled up. The grass is mowed. Plants and bushes are trimmed. It's not a neighborhood that looks fancy, but it feels like a good place to raise a family. It is quiet, peaceful, and safe.

There is a sheriff's department and jail, a health department, and a recycling center nearby. We have baseball and softball fields, and a small airport.  You can hear the planes taking off and landing. There is a local ice cream shop you can walk to. You can also walk to downtown. My kids can ride their bikes to the park, which is just a few blocks away. It is a very nice place to live.
